or straight.

524
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:34,146
Oh, my God, you are so quick
to judge everyone.

525
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:36,314
You want to label everyone up
against some old stereotype.

526
00:18:36,348 --> 00:18:39,201
You are the most stereotypical
person I've ever met in my life.

527
00:18:39,235 --> 00:18:41,352
What do you care what anyone is?
Why do you care what I am?

528
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,521
Because I like you.
Because I'm d...

529
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:45,707
I'm drawn to you.

530
00:18:48,211 --> 00:18:50,361
I really loved my husband,
Edgar.

531
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,047
I really did.

532
00:18:52,081 --> 00:18:53,698
We had the best time together.

533
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:55,834
We would go to the theater,

534
00:18:55,868 --> 00:18:58,470
we would discover new bistros.

535
00:18:58,504 --> 00:19:00,839
I was so attracted to all that.

536
00:19:02,225 --> 00:19:06,377
But Edgar was not attracted...
To me.

537
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:11,216
And I do not want to make
that same mistake twice.

538
00:19:11,234 --> 00:19:13,819
Jane, the world has changed.

539
00:19:13,853 --> 00:19:15,687
It's not black and white
anymore.

540
00:19:15,721 --> 00:19:18,073
Well, maybe it's just too much
change for me.

541
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,576
(Knocks on desk)

542
00:19:21,611 --> 00:19:22,727
Sit down.

543
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:26,564
I can help you change
your hair,

544
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:28,867
I can help you
change your outfit,

545
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:30,335
but only you can
change yourself.

546
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:31,903
The question you have to ask is

547
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:34,923
do you want to hold onto the way
things used to be and be right,

548
00:19:34,957 --> 00:19:37,576
or do you want to
change and be happy?

549
00:19:45,768 --> 00:19:47,435
You still think I'm gay?

550
00:19:47,470 --> 00:19:48,937
(Moans)

551
00:19:51,557 --> 00:19:53,225
I don't care.

552
00:19:55,263 --> 00:19:57,690
So, I have been thinking about
the outfit

553
00:19:57,724 --> 00:19:59,742
our baby will wear
for the birth announcement.

554
00:19:59,776 --> 00:20:02,578
Oh, sweetie, I really don't
want this to be a whole thing.

555
00:20:02,612 --> 00:20:05,063
So he can wear whatever
you want him to wear.

556
00:20:08,918 --> 00:20:11,370
What made you change your mind?

557
00:20:11,404 --> 00:20:12,621
That silly dinner party.

558
00:20:12,672 --> 00:20:16,008
Last night, I became that kid
from junior high all over again.

559
00:20:16,042 --> 00:20:18,711
Judging someone because I was
afraid of being judged.

560
00:20:18,745 --> 00:20:20,345
It wasn't just you.

561
00:20:20,380 --> 00:20:21,747
It was Shania, too.

562
00:20:21,765 --> 00:20:23,382
(Chuckles)

563
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:26,051
If we don't change,
if we don't evolve, then we die.

564
00:20:26,085 --> 00:20:28,721
You don't see any theropod
dinosaurs hanging around

565
00:20:28,755 --> 00:20:30,773
anymore, do you?
You want to know why?

566
00:20:30,807 --> 00:20:31,940
Because dromaeosauridae...

567
00:20:31,975 --> 00:20:33,992
Oh, my God, David,
it's like you want me

568
00:20:34,027 --> 00:20:36,428
to stop paying attention.

569
00:20:37,614 --> 00:20:39,782
I just don't want our son

570
00:20:39,816 --> 00:20:41,917
to grow up the way that I did:

571
00:20:41,951 --> 00:20:43,569
Afraid to be myself,

572
00:20:43,603 --> 00:20:46,271
playing into stereotypes
so he won't be judged.

573
00:20:46,289 --> 00:20:49,875
But he can only do that
if I'm not afraid.

574
00:20:49,909 --> 00:20:52,010
So, go ahead.

575
00:20:52,045 --> 00:20:55,881
Put our son in
the dress... gown.

576
00:20:55,915 --> 00:20:58,784
But I do have one
slight adjustment.

577
00:21:03,623 --> 00:21:05,557
(Laughs)

578
00:21:05,592 --> 00:21:06,958
It's perfect.

579
00:21:06,976 --> 00:21:11,072
It's odd and amazing,
and it will confuse everyone.

580
00:21:11,947 --> 00:21:13,202
And I love it.

